"{\"uid\": \"inews.co.uk-sport-olympics-team-gb-first-medal-paris-olympics-synchro-divers-win-bronze-3193436\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"IMPARTIAL NEWS + INTELLIGENT DEBATE  Account  Scarlett Mew Jensen and Yasmin Harper picked up bronze before Anna Henderson's surprise silver in the women's time trial  PARIS - Anna Henderson earnedTeam GB'sfirst silver of the Games with a narrow second place in the women's individual time-trial cycling.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 304, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 46, \"end\": 65, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Scarlett_Mew_Jensen\", \"score\": 0.9999999999977263, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Scarlett Mew Jensen\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Scarlett_Mew_Jensen\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Scarlett_Mew_Jensen\"}, {\"begin\": 108, \"end\": 122, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anna_Henderson\", \"score\": 0.9999958972009645, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Anna Henderson\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anna_Henderson\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anna_Henderson\"}, {\"begin\": 176, \"end\": 190, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anna_Henderson\", \"score\": 0.9999958972009645, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Anna Henderson\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anna_Henderson\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anna_Henderson\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Henderson finished with a time of 41:09.83 behind Australia's Grace Brown, eclipsing American Chloe Dygert by just a second.\", \"from\": 306, \"to\": 430, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 306, \"end\": 315, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gerald_Henderson_Jr.\", \"score\": 0.9999998166749887, \"rank\": 8.964495542197147e-08, \"text\": \"Henderson\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q3665646\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gerald_Henderson_Jr.\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gerald_Henderson_Jr.\"}, {\"begin\": 356, \"end\": 365, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia_men's_national_rugby_league_team\", \"score\": 0.8768464770900912, \"rank\": 0.12192787031213358, \"text\": \"Australia\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia_men's_national_rugby_league_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia_men's_national_rugby_league_team\"}, {\"begin\": 368, \"end\": 379, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Murder_of_Grace_Brown\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.9901691969529914e-14, \"text\": \"Grace Brown\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Murder_of_Grace_Brown\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Murder_of_Grace_Brown\"}, {\"begin\": 391, \"end\": 399, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9995340719465248, \"rank\": 0.0002467346763724368, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It has been a long road to glory for Brown, who has twice finished as runner-up at World Championships but this time was in a league of her own, eclipsing Henderson by a minute and a half.\", \"from\": 431, \"to\": 619, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 586, \"end\": 595, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gerald_Henderson_Jr.\", \"score\": 0.9999998166749887, \"rank\": 8.964495542197147e-08, \"text\": \"Henderson\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q3665646\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gerald_Henderson_Jr.\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gerald_Henderson_Jr.\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The British rider was in fact something of a latecomer to cycling, and excelled as a national champion in skiing as a youngster, which perhaps helped her stay upright in treacherous conditions.\", \"from\": 621, \"to\": 814, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 625, \"end\": 632, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"score\": 0.9941834189818226, \"rank\": 0.003535846725079156, \"text\": \"British\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I did not realise how slippery it was out there until I was already on the course,\\\" Henderson said afterwards.\", \"from\": 816, \"to\": 927, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 901, \"end\": 910, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gerald_Henderson_Jr.\", \"score\": 0.9999998166749887, \"rank\": 8.964495542197147e-08, \"text\": \"Henderson\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q3665646\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gerald_Henderson_Jr.\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gerald_Henderson_Jr.\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I thought 'I could lose the whole Olympic Games in one corner here' and you gain all your time in the straights.\", \"from\": 929, \"to\": 1042, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"So I really took control and my coach did a really good job to keep me calm the whole way through.\", \"from\": 1043, \"to\": 1141, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Last year I was two seconds from the bronze in worlds so I am really happy to be on the right side of the seconds this time.\\\"\", \"from\": 1143, \"to\": 1269, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Her silver added to what had already been a special day for British athletes, with Scarlett Mew Jensen and Yasmin Harper picking up the nation's first medal - a bronze - in the 3m springboard synchronised diving event.\", \"from\": 1271, \"to\": 1489, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1331, \"end\": 1338, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"score\": 0.9941834189818226, \"rank\": 0.003535846725079156, \"text\": \"British\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\"}, {\"begin\": 1354, \"end\": 1373, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Scarlett_Mew_Jensen\", \"score\": 0.9999999999977263, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Scarlett Mew Jensen\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Scarlett_Mew_Jensen\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Scarlett_Mew_Jensen\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"They claimed it thanks to a \\\"shocking\\\" blow-up from Australia to earn GB's first opening-day medal in 20 years, since Pete Waterfield and Leon Taylor's silver in the 10m sychro at Athens.\", \"from\": 1491, \"to\": 1678, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1543, \"end\": 1552, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia_men's_national_rugby_league_team\", \"score\": 0.8768464770900912, \"rank\": 0.12192787031213358, \"text\": \"Australia\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia_men's_national_rugby_league_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia_men's_national_rugby_league_team\"}, {\"begin\": 1561, \"end\": 1563, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"score\": 0.8840142670712471, \"rank\": 0.13120344363694586, \"text\": \"GB\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\"}, {\"begin\": 1629, \"end\": 1640, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Leon_Taylor\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Leon Taylor\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Leon_Taylor\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Leon_Taylor\"}, {\"begin\": 1671, \"end\": 1677, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2004_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9999999998985913, \"rank\": 1.0146020944639245e-10, \"text\": \"Athens\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2004_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2004_Summer_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Harper - on her Olympic debut - and Mew Jensen were in fourth place going into the final dive of the morning and their score of 70.68 for their three-and-a-half pike somersault did not look enough.\", \"from\": 1680, \"to\": 1877, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"But then came Maddison Keeney and Annabele Smith and their two-and-a-half somersault twist, a small degree of difficulty lower than the British pair.\", \"from\": 1879, \"to\": 2028, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1893, \"end\": 1908, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Maddison_Keeney\", \"score\": 0.9999999320498342, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Maddison Keeney\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Maddison_Keeney\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Maddison_Keeney\"}, {\"begin\": 2015, \"end\": 2022, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"score\": 0.9941834189818226, \"rank\": 0.003535846725079156, \"text\": \"British\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"And they landed an audible distance from synchronisation: the two cracks as they hit the water was easily noticeable.\", \"from\": 2030, \"to\": 2147, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The crowd were stunned into silence - one Australian journalist exclaimed an elongated \\\"f**k\\\".\", \"from\": 2148, \"to\": 2242, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2190, \"end\": 2200, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia_men's_national_rugby_league_team\", \"score\": 0.8821623645709302, \"rank\": 0.09238847861737459, \"text\": \"Australian\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia_men's_national_rugby_league_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia_men's_national_rugby_league_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Mew Jensen and Harper still had three more dives to watch before the medal was confirmed - and when it was, the pair leapt and hugged their coaching staff.\", \"from\": 2244, \"to\": 2399, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"They now have an Olympic medal to match their bronze at last year's World Championships.\", \"from\": 2400, \"to\": 2488, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Mew Jensen said: \\\"We knew that even after our last dive that we would still be on the back foot and we knew that Australia needed to mess up.\", \"from\": 2490, \"to\": 2631, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2603, \"end\": 2612, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia_men's_national_rugby_league_team\", \"score\": 0.8768464770900912, \"rank\": 0.12192787031213358, \"text\": \"Australia\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia_men's_national_rugby_league_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia_men's_national_rugby_league_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"For that to actually happen, we were very, very shocked because that is a very easy dive for them, they are very talented, very experienced.\", \"from\": 2632, \"to\": 2772, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"It was very, very shocking.\", \"from\": 2774, \"to\": 2802, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"But we needed to deliver towards the end.\\\"\", \"from\": 2803, \"to\": 2845, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Harper, who turns 24 on Monday, added: \\\"We knew it was going to be tight and to watch them not perform on the last round\\u2026 I think I knew straight away [after the Australians' dive] that it wasn't enough.\", \"from\": 2847, \"to\": 3050, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"But you are still waiting for that scoreboard to pop up.\\\"\", \"from\": 3051, \"to\": 3108, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It was GB's first ever medal at this discipline - and their first female diving medal in 64 years.\", \"from\": 3110, \"to\": 3208, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3117, \"end\": 3119, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"score\": 0.8840142670712471, \"rank\": 0.13120344363694586, \"text\": \"GB\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It underlines the depth of talent in the sport.\", \"from\": 3209, \"to\": 3256, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"We still have the likes of Andrea Spendolini-Sirieux, Tom Daley and Jack Laugher to come at the aquatic centre.\", \"from\": 3258, \"to\": 3369, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3312, \"end\": 3321, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tom_Daley\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.2735592902329184e-59, \"text\": \"Tom Daley\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tom_Daley\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tom_Daley\"}, {\"begin\": 3326, \"end\": 3338, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jack_Laugher\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Jack Laugher\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jack_Laugher\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jack_Laugher\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Australians, meanwhile, will want to forget this day.\", \"from\": 3370, \"to\": 3427, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"China were untouchable and close to flawless, with Yani Chang and Yiwen Chen finishing 23 points ahead of USA's Sarah Bacon and Kassidy Cook.\", \"from\": 3429, \"to\": 3570, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3429, \"end\": 3434, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"score\": 0.8858735611109629, \"rank\": 0.1034138137193111, \"text\": \"China\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\"}, {\"begin\": 3501, \"end\": 3505, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chen_Shui-bian\", \"score\": 0.9752431726824619, \"rank\": 0.025200863343996016, \"text\": \"Chen\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chen_Shui-bian\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chen_Shui-bian\"}, {\"begin\": 3535, \"end\": 3538, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9802760015469701, \"rank\": 0.018788999827123662, \"text\": \"USA\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 3541, \"end\": 3552, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sarah_Bacon\", \"score\": 0.9999783626862015, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Sarah Bacon\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sarah_Bacon\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sarah_Bacon\"}, {\"begin\": 3557, \"end\": 3569, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kassidy_Cook\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Kassidy Cook\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kassidy_Cook\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kassidy_Cook\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Impartial news + intelligent debate  All rights reserved.\", \"from\": 3572, \"to\": 3629, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00a9 2026 Associated Newspapers Limited.\", \"from\": 3630, \"to\": 3667, \"entities\": []}]}"